            <p>Those with Switch consoles who have had a hankering to play <a href="https://www.eurogamer.net/games/tomb-raider-definitive-edition">Tomb Raider: Definitive Edition</a> - that is to say, <a href="https://www.digitalfoundry.net/articles/digitalfoundry-2014-tomb-raider-definitive-performance-analysis">the remaster of 2013's Tomb Raider reboot</a> - but have been unable to do so due to its lack of availability, well I have good news for you.</p>
<p>Today, Aspyr and Crystal Dynamics shadow dropped the game on Switch and <a href="https://www.eurogamer.net/platforms/switch-2">Switch 2</a>. You can check out a trailer for it below.</p>

